  "prompt": "If you call someone on whatsapp by mistake and instantly hang up, does it still give them a missed call notification?",
  "response": "Yes, generally when you call someone on WhatsApp\u2014even if you hang up immediately after initiating the call\u2014the recipient will receive a missed call notification. Here's how it typically works:\n\n1. **Call Attempt Registration**: When you initiate a WhatsApp call, the app sends a signal to the recipient's device indicating that there's an incoming call. This happens almost instantaneously once the call is made.\n\n2. **Missed Call Notification**: If the recipient does not answer the call (whether intentionally or accidentally), WhatsApp logs this as a missed call and notifies the user accordingly. The duration of the call doesn't usually matter; even a call lasting less than a second can trigger this notification.\n\n3. **Possible Exceptions**:\n    - **Network Delays**: In rare cases, if there are significant network issues on either end, the call might not register properly, and a missed call notification might not be sent.\n    - **App or Device Glitches**: Occasionally, bugs or glitches within the app or the device's operating system might prevent the missed call notification from appearing.\n    - **Recipient's Settings**: If the recipient has customized their notification settings to suppress certain alerts or if they have Do Not Disturb enabled, they might not receive the missed call notification as usual.\n\n4. **Privacy Considerations**: It's worth noting that while WhatsApp notifies users of missed calls, it doesn't reveal whether the call was answered or declined unless the user interacts with the notification. This means accidental quick hang-ups won't inform the caller about the recipient's response beyond the missed call indicator.\n\n5. **Best Practices**:\n    - **Double-Check Before Calling**: To avoid unintended missed call notifications, it's a good practice to ensure you're calling the right contact before initiating the call.\n    - **Communicate If Needed**: If you frequently make accidental calls, consider informing your contacts to prevent any potential confusion.\n\nIn summary, while there might be extremely rare scenarios where an almost instantaneous hang-up doesn't trigger a missed call notification, under normal circumstances, WhatsApp will notify the recipient of the missed call regardless of how brief the call was.",
